",\"text\":\"**Considering Spring Boot setup**\\n\\nI’m analyzing the new Spring Boot module, which likely includes boot-test. For the spring-boot-amqp issue, I'm curious about setting deterministic dependencies, though that might not be relevant. Adding spring-boot-test could enhance test coverage, especially since the user is asking about setup beyond the usual test scaffold.\\n\\nIt seems like H2 could be concrete evidence needed. Also, do I require the dependency org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test:4.1.0 for better coverage? I'll need to check if I need to add org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-actuator:4.1.0 for coverage of the main package with H2.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating actuator endpoints and setup**\\n\\nI'm considering whether to reference optional actuator endpoint classes or not. It seems the generator should typically avoid this unless actuator or auto-configuration is being added. The risk of uncovering these optional classes appears low.\\n\\nI need to pick `advisory_preparation` for a deterministic H2 setup. The guidance suggests setting up an in-memory H2 datasource with specific configurations. Also, I wonder if I should enable analytics for Liquibase; it looks like I need to set `spring.liquibase.analytics-enabled=false` in test properties to avoid telemetry. Is this extra setup necessary? It doesn't seem required for coverage, but it's a good precaution.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Spring Boot Liquibase auto-configuration only becomes meaningful when Liquibase can run against a JDBC DataSource; the resolved artifact brings Spring Boot JDBC and liquibase-core but no database driver.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"com.h2database:h2:2.4.240\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Spring Boot Liquibase normally runs database migrations against a DataSource. H2 provides an in-memory JDBC database so generated tests can exercise LiquibaseAutoConfiguration and actual changelog execution without Docker.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use a small in-memory H2 setup and test changelog. Either place a changelog at the default `classpath:/db/changelog/db.changelog-master.yaml` or set `spring.liquibase.change-log` to a test resource. Configure a deterministic test datasource such as `spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:liquibase-test;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1`, `spring.datasource.username=sa`, and consider `spring.liquibase.analytics-enabled=false` to keep tests hermetic.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact also contains optional actuator, Docker Compose, and Testcontainers integration classes; broad coverage of those optional paths may need additional optional Spring Boot/Testcontainers dependencies, but they are not required for initial meaningful Liquibase auto-configuration coverage.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for the exact H2 version and any native-image reachability gaps.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_001bea7949f061af016a3eeb04ba2c8195bc0e72e0814e69f0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1401, "output": 857, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41682, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782508281442, "responseId": "resp_001bea7949f061af016a3eeaf9e7bc819594293de0bc5491c0"}, "toolResults": []}
